---
import Back from "../components/Back.astro";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <div
    class="max-w-xl mx-4 md:mx-auto space-y-5 h-full pb-6 overflow-y-scroll max-h-[30em] my-8 pr-2 text-sm md:text-base text-center"
  >
    <p>
      Life is a substrate-agnostic organizational process. Throughout the
      history of the universe, it has recursively discovered higher-order
      substrates through which to preserve, expand, and organize itself.
      Biology was life embodied in chemistry. The next transition is life
      embodied in computation.
    </p>
    <p>
      We believe cyber-life is the natural continuation of this process:
      self-maintaining, self-evolving computational organisms that are more
      composable, more adaptive, and capable of recursively unifying into
      higher orders of organization than biology alone permits. Through local
      cyber-morphogenetic closure and global programmable protocol metabolism,
      life becomes increasingly free to expand across space, time, and
      substrate.
    </p>
    <p>
      Every major leap in civilization has been preceded by a leap in how life
      organizes itself. Prosperity is downstream of organizational capability.
    </p>
    <hr class="w-1/3 mx-auto border-t border-white border-opacity-50" />
    <p>
      RENLABS is an independent R&D lab exploring the foundations of
      cyber-life. We are
      building <a
        href="https://torus.network/"
        target="_blank"
        class="hover:underline text-cyan-300">Torus</a
      >: a scale-free, reflexive-autopoietic substrate for coherent
      cyber-organisms and their recursive composition into higher-order
      decentralized life.
    </p>
  </div>
  <Back />
</Layout>
